17 except for any ad valorem taxes to pay interest on and to retire county school district
18 bonded indebtedness.
19 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
20 the O.C.G.A., as amended.
21 (b) Each resident of the Lowndes County school district who is 65 years of age or older on
22 or before January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption required by
23 subsection (d) of this section is made is granted an exemption on such person's homestead
24 from Lowndes County school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the
25 amount of $40,000.00 of the assessed value of such homestead. The value of that property
26 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
27 (c) Each resident of the Lowndes County school district who is 70 years of age or older on
28 or before January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption required by
29 subsection (d) of this section is made is granted an exemption on such person's homestead
30 from Lowndes County school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the
31 amount of $50,000.00 of the assessed value of such homestead. The value of that property
32 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
33 (d)(1) Except as provided for in paragraph (2) of this subsection, a person shall not
34 receive the homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) or (c) of this section unless
35 such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner of Lowndes
36 County, giving such information relative to receiving such exemption as will enable the
37 tax commissioner of Lowndes County to make a determination regarding the initial and
38 continuing eligibility of such person for such exemption. The tax commissioner of
39 Lowndes County shall provide application forms for this purpose.
40 (2) Each resident of the Lowndes County school district 65 years of age or older allowed
41 the $10,000.00 homestead exemption on such resident's homestead from Lowndes
42 County school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes granted by the
43 amendment to the Constitution of the State of Georgia applicable to residents of Lowndes
